<paragraph id="679194CB4A42CC76AE8092D2CB2B81B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The type material (TN: 723 SEMJ) has been deposited in Sindh Entomological Museum, Department of Zoology, University of Sindh, Jamshoro.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6A7A4CF7E8441D9CAC5AE78E7722C4ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="14620839B5A33C63E42C8844AD47ED95" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="185C1F98D67E3ADC8D4466AB85ED71FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="8C4FC9683701569990F8FC2CE477FDB4" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Modicogryllus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Modicogryllus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F4599A161FC60A904EA6E8A8334F77E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Modicogryllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erected by 
<bibRefCitation id="C1A0B9A8E7AB9994987FA814A7241B6B" author="Chopard, L" journalOrPublisher="Publicacoes Culturais" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="15 - 69" refId="B4" refString="Chopard, L, 1961. Orthopteres Gryllidae et Gryllacrididae l'Angola. Companhia de Diamantes de Angola. Publicacoes Culturais 56: 15 - 69" title="Orthopteres Gryllidae et Gryllacrididae l'Angola. Companhia de Diamantes de Angola." volume="56" year="1961">Chopard (1961)</bibRefCitation>
, within which he described four species from north-east part of India viz: 
<taxonomicName id="7C487EA6A16962C28F74933B59A1229B" genus="M." lsidName="M. semiobscurus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="semiobscurus">
<emphasis id="EE9D47274B8CE83EB45A20346552A540" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. semiobscurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chopard), 
<taxonomicName id="F63152C6D298E3EDC3E3AA5B0E955EAE" genus="M." lsidName="M. ehsani" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ehsani">
<emphasis id="BC0A2D8D872546AD260FBDC22C9E2D2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. ehsani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chopard), 
<taxonomicName id="BDD6BDC91AB1F720C2FE256292FDC6B2" genus="M." lsidName="M. rehni" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="rehni">
<emphasis id="586A412EB7161C8083702950F57625E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. rehni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chopard), and 
<taxonomicName id="2E1E471377CF6F9CB965696F344DFAD1" genus="M." lsidName="M. minimus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis id="EA82487ACF86C19B0667A86C0ACF96FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Chopard). Our collected species has a brightly coloured body along with a shiny pronotum. The tegmina and wing show different patches on their entire surface. However, the shape, length, and other characteristics of the ovipositor make it different from the other species in the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
